{{Infobox artwork/wikidata |image = Trains Mural by Jeff and Gregory Ackers Columbus, Ohio 1989 01.jpg |caption = A portion of the ''Trains'' mural.}}
'''''Trains''''' is a mural in [[the Short North]] and [[Italian Village, Columbus, Ohio|Italian Village]] neighborhoods in [[Columbus, Ohio]].
== History == Created by Jeff and [[Gregory Ackers]] in 1989, it covers the south wall of Bernard's Tavern and depicts passengers (some who are British royalty) on a train arriving in Columbus' [[Union Station (Columbus, Ohio)|Union Station]].
It is across the parking lot of another Ackers-created mural, [[Union Station (mural)|''Union Station'']] <ref name=NYT>[http://www.thisweeknews.com/content/stories/clintonville/news/2012/03/27/artist-selected-for-planned-mural.html "Artist Selected for Planned Mural"], Kevin Parks. This Week Community News. 28 mar 2012. Retrieved 20 jun 2012.</ref>
As of 2014, a building is being built on the space that served as a parking lot and the mural can no longer be seen.
